AUM-Ø Metal kernels — attribution
==================================

This directory builds the AUM-Ø Apple-Silicon (Metal/MPS) kernels standalone, with no dependency
on the ThunderMittens repository at build or runtime.

Vendored substrate (header-only MSL, in ./include/):
  Derived from ThunderMittens (an Apple Metal Shading Language port of ThunderKittens,
  HazyResearch, https://github.com/HazyResearch/ThunderKittens). These are the reusable
  tile/type/op primitives (`tk.metal` and the common/, ops/, types/ trees). Periodically synced
  from the ThunderMittens working tree; unmodified here.

Kernel sources (in ./src/):
  - mamba2.metal      : SSD forward (quadratic materialized, D in {64,128}), the chunked
                        LINEAR-TIME 3-kernel pipeline (ssd_chunk_kv/scan/out, D=64), and the
                        backward (mamba2_bwd_row/col with in-kernel fp32 dcumlog row/col sums,
                        D in {64,128}). Vendored verbatim from ThunderMittens' mamba2 kernel.

Host dispatch (./aum_metal.mm) and build (./__init__.py):
  Written for AUM-Ø; the generic torch-MPS encoder/plumbing follows ThunderMittens' tk_torch
  pattern (torch::mps command-stream dispatch), inlined here so the build is self-contained.

